The paper deals with generating visual features using a conditional generative model that combines VAE and GANs for any-shot learning problems. The focus is on image classification datasets, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of generative models and machine learning techniques such as VAE and GANs suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with learning class conditional distributions and generating textual arguments, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with visualizing features and interpreting them, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
